PROJECTS 
FAKE NEWS DETECTION USING OPEN-SOURCE PYTHON MACHINE LEARNING LIBRARIES 
•Using open-source Python libraries, created an application that can detect whether a given piece of news text 
is real or fake. 
•
Used sklearn library to extract the Tf-Idf vector from the given text, which is piped into a classifier model. 
•Used an open-source labelled dataset for training and testing the classifier model. 
•
Python libraries used were — numpy, sklearn, and jupyter. 
BRAIN TUMOUR DETECTION USING DIGITAL IMAGE PROCESSING — BACHELORS THESIS WORK, 2020 
•Using digitally processed MRI scans of brain images, we created an application to detect whether the tumour 
is benign or malignant. 
•The algorithm uses an SVM classifier on a feature set extracted using K-means clustering. 
•
Developed the algorithm on Matlab using existing ML libraries. 
•Collaborated with 3 of my peers to execute and present the project to the thesis evaluation panel.

ENVIRONMENT HEALTH MONITORING USING IOT — 2019 
•
Using temperature, humidity, UV, and PM2.5 sensors, created an active weather monitoring unit on Raspberry 
Pi that can monitor and alert on various weather parameters based on configured thresholds. 
•Used Python scripts to interface the unit, pushing the values periodically into a central database that can be 
queried from the internet. 
•Collaborated with 3 of my classmates to execute and present the project to a college-wide forum.
